snippet.textDisplay:
I have never seen the man so relieved than after hitting that last D10. After winning the UK Open (great achievement that, btw), he didn't look like a player who finally won a major. He actually talked it down himself, because the best players didn't take part in it. Every other on-stage win-reaction looked more like anger towards himself - "Why can't you do that all the time you useless [...]". It frustrated the hell out of him and out of me too for sure.
During this tournament, you could literally see how Wright got more self-assured with every round. Every single one of his opponents kept raising their game, kept coming back at him. Against Malicdem he was kinda lucky, but got himself out of there with skill from the heavens. Didn't play great against Asada, but more controlled. After the win against de Zwaan, I was sure he would win this tournament. So much coolness under pressure against an excellent opponent. And even though Humphries and Price were always close to him, I felt an inevetability about Wright coming out on top. The final was just pure and brutal confidence. Only two real mistakes, missing darts at double in the first and the last set, which he both won anyway. Van Gerwen just played a machine yesterday.
I do believe that the confidence of "having done it" will stick with him this time. Looking forward to the best Peter Wright so far from this day onwards. Good luck Peter Wright!

And a happy new year to all you Darts fans out there.

Every other on-stage win-reaction looked more like anger towards himself - "Why can't you do that all the time you useless [...]". It frustrated the hell out of him and out of me too for sure.
During this tournament, you could literally see how Wright got more self-assured with every round. Every single one of his opponents kept raising their game, kept coming back at him. Against Malicdem he was kinda lucky, but got himself out of there with skill from the heavens. Didn't play great against Asada, but more controlled. After the win against de Zwaan, I was sure he would win this tournament. So much coolness under pressure against an excellent opponent. And even though Humphries and Price were always close to him, I felt an inevetability about Wright coming out on top. The final was just pure and brutal confidence. Only two real mistakes, missing darts at double in the first and the last set, which he both won anyway. Van Gerwen just played a machine yesterday.
I do believe that the confidence of "having done it" will stick with him this time. Looking forward to the best Peter Wright so far from this day onwards. Good luck Peter Wright! 

And a happy new year to all you Darts fans out there.
